OL,3,CGuernsey considering second phase of
OL,4,Cnew offences to new domestic abuse law
OL,6,FGuernsey's Committee for Home Affairs
OL,7,Fhas confirmed it is considering adding
OL,8,Fa second phase of offences to its new
OL,9,Fdomestic abuse law.
OL,11,FIt will include making actions such
OL,12,Fas; non-fatal strangulation, stalking
OL,13,Fand drink spiking an offence under the
OL,14,Fnew legislation.
OL,16,FThe committee say they are also keen
OL,17,Fto create a register for domestic
OL,18,Fabuse offenders.
